<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/520: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-05T14:00:00-05:00">October 5, 1937—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. Your 188, October 4, 1 p.m. Inasmuch as the substance of the
                            Department’s telegram no. 92 [<hi rend="italic">91</hi>] of September
                            30, 5 p.m. has been conveyed to Ambassador Espil,<note n="7" xml:id="d219fn7">Felipe A. Espil, Argentine Ambassador in the United
                                States.</note> with a view to enlisting his support of the program
                            therein outlined, it is believed that you may wish to present the
                            memorandum now without further delay, particularly in view of the last
                            paragraph of your telegram no. 167, September 7, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>